article.description: Wayne Chism scored a career-high 27 points, Tyler Smith added 23 and Tennessee beat Auburn 94-85 Saturday to advance to its first Southeastern Conference championship game in nearly 20 years.
article.headline: Chism has career-high 27 points as Volunteers top Tigers for berth in SEC final
article.linkText: Vols get past Auburn for rare spot in SEC final

inlines.body:
Fast Facts

• Tennessee advanced to the SEC championship game for the first time since 1991.

• Wayne Chism scored a career-high 27 points and Tyler Smith added 23; Smith has scored 20+ points in three of the last four games.

• Tennessee will face Mississippi State in the finals, a team the Vols have beaten five straight times.

• The loss ends a five-game win streak for Auburn.

-- ESPN research

article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- Wayne Chism scored a career-high 27 points, Tyler Smith added 23 and Tennessee beat Auburn 94-85 Saturday to advance to its first Southeastern Conference championship game in 18 years. The Volunteers (21-11) will play surging Mississippi State in the final. The Bulldogs are 7-1 against teams from the conference's Eastern Division, with the one loss coming at Tennessee in late February. The Vols can only hope to play as well as they did against Auburn, especially in the first half. Tennessee shot 62 percent from the field and 58 percent from 3-point range in the opening 20 minutes while opening up a 14-point lead. The Tigers (22-11) cut it to 55-50 early in the second half, but the Vols pulled away down the stretch. Korvotney Barber led Auburn with 24 points and nine rebounds. Rasheem Barrett added 18, and Tay Waller chipped in 17.
